\n   179→\"Explain this module as if onboarding a new engineer\"\n   180→\"Summarize this PR in architectural terms\"\n   181→\"What assumptions does this service make?\"\n   182→\\`\\`\\`\n   183→\n   184→Documentation stops being an afterthought and becomes a **byproduct of thinking**.\n   185→\n   186→---\n   187→\n   188→## The Cultural Shift (The Hard Part)\n   189→\n   190→Tools don't change teams.\n   191→Expectations do.\n   192→\n   193→This way of working only functions if:\n   194→\n   195→- Ownership is non-negotiable\n   196→- \"AI wrote it\" is never an excuse\n   197→- Slower decisions are acceptable under uncertainty\n   198→- Engineers are evaluated on clarity, not output volume\n   199→\n   200→AI amplifies both good and bad engineering habits.\n   201→If the culture is weak, AI accelerates the collapse.\n   202→\n   203→---\n   204→\n   205→## The Result\n   206→\n   207→The outcome isn't magical productivity gains.\n   208→\n   209→It's something better:\n   210→\n   211→- Fewer production surprises\n   212→- Less heroism, more consistency\n   213→- Code that can be explained, not just executed\n   214→- Teams that scale without burning seniors\n   215→\n   216→This isn't the future of work.\n   217→It's the correction we should have made years ago.\n   218→\n   219→And it's still a work in progress.`,\n   220→    date: \"2025-07-15\",\n   221→    readTime: \"8 min read\",\n   222→    tags: [\"ai\", \"code-quality\", \"testing\", \"documentation\", \"engineering-culture\"],\n   223→    slug: \"new-way-of-working-ai-code-quality-testing-documentation\"\n   224→  },\n   225→  {\n   226→    id: \"1\",\n   227→    title: \".NET 9 Telemetry: pushing logs and metrics to HELK with OpenTelemetry\",\n   228→    excerpt: \"Modern observability: sending .NET 9 telemetry to HELK with OpenTelemetry for logs, traces, and metrics.\",\n   229→    content: `# .NET 9 Telemetry: pushing logs and metrics to HELK with OpenTelemetry\n   230→\n   231→*14 Nov 2024 — Min